<TITLE> President hosts reception on Janmashtami </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 4 (bdnews24.com) -- President Iajuddin Ahmed and his wife Professor Anwara Begum Tuesday hosted a reception to the Hindu community at Bangabhaban on the occasion of Janmashtami, a major religious festival. Religious affairs adviser ASM Matiur Rahman, Indian deputy high commissioner, the charge d' affaires of Nepal, representatives of international organisations and distinguished members of the Hindu community attended the reception. The president and his wife welcomed the guests, exchanged pleasantries and wished all a happy and prosperous future. Janmashtami is the Hindu festival celebrating the birth of Lord Krishna, an avatar of Vishnu. bdnews24
